# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# .dockerignore for apps/api
#
# Evaluated RELATIVE TO THE BUILD CONTEXT (the monorepo root, because we build
# with `docker build -f apps/api/Dockerfile .` from the repo root and flyctl
# uploads the monorepo as the build context).
#
# Rationale: every path that stays out of the image keeps the layer hash
# stable and trims build uploads to Fly's remote builder.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Dependency graphs — reinstalled fresh inside the builder stage
**/node_modules
**/.pnpm-store

# VCS metadata
.git
.gitignore
.gitattributes
**/.github

# Build outputs — recreated inside the image
**/dist
**/build
**/.turbo
**/.next
**/.vercel
**/out

# Editor / IDE / OS cruft
.vscode
.idea
.cursor
.claude
**/.DS_Store
**/Thumbs.db

# Test artefacts
**/coverage
**/*.test.ts
**/*.test.tsx
**/*.test.js
**/*.spec.ts
**/*.spec.tsx
**/*.spec.js
**/__tests__
**/__mocks__
**/e2e
**/playwright-report
**/test-results

# Local environment files — secrets ship via `flyctl secrets set`
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# Logs & dumps
**/*.log
**/npm-debug.log*
**/pnpm-debug.log*
**/yarn-debug.log*
**/yarn-error.log*

# Docs (not needed at runtime; keep images small)
**/*.md
LICENSE
docs
README*

# Web app source — API image doesn't need it
apps/web

# Drizzle local artefacts (migrations are applied out-of-band by deploy.yml)
**/drizzle/meta/_journal.json.lock

# Misc tooling caches
**/.eslintcache
**/.parcel-cache
**/tsconfig.tsbuildinfo
